Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.77,0:00:06.97,Magus-Internal/narrator,Edgelady,0000,0000,0000,,I've lived in this world for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.32,0:00:09.33,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,I see. You're leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.66,0:00:10.73,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Be well.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.73,0:00:13.28,Magus-Flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,Oh look, it's the failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.28,0:00:14.56,Magus-Flashback,B,0000,0000,0000,,Don't bother with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.56,0:00:18.05,Magus-Flashback,Angelidad,0000,0000,0000,,This is my daughter, Angelica.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.50,0:00:19.58,Magus-Flashback,Angelica,0000,0000,0000,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.85,0:00:22.74,Magus-Flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,Poor half-assed monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.97,0:00:25.95,Magus-Flashback,Priest,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you, though we may \Nnot know each other for long.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.50,0:00:34.71,Magus-Internal/narrator,Edgelady,0000,0000,0000,,The only one who would look just at me
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.81,0:00:38.45,Magus-Internal/narrator,Edgelady,0000,0000,0000,,was you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.47,0:02:20.35,Default,PersonA,0000,0000,0000,,Have you heard? A dragon went on a rampage.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.35,0:02:22.21,Default,PersonB,0000,0000,0000,,Where? London?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.21,0:02:25.98,Default,PersonA,0000,0000,0000,,I heard a human child tamed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.98,0:02:27.72,Default,PersonC,0000,0000,0000,,Not bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.72,0:02:29.06,Default,PersonD,0000,0000,0000,,Who did that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.90,0:02:33.04,Default,PersonA,0000,0000,0000,,It's that Sleigh Beggy who can talk to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.36,0:02:35.77,Default,SideM,0000,0000,0000,,Here, work on this, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.77,0:02:36.68,Default,Blonde,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.68,0:02:37.97,Default,SideM,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.97,0:02:41.71,Default,SideM,0000,0000,0000,,I'll leave a note for Tory, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.41,0:02:44.45,Default,Blonde,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.45,0:02:47.48,Default,SideM,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think I've slept much since then.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.90,0:02:50.12,Default,Blonde,0000,0000,0000,,So you aren't okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.12,0:02:51.73,Default,Blonde,0000,0000,0000,,Do you need anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.01,0:02:54.58,Default,SideM,0000,0000,0000,,A bowl of mashed potatoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.58,0:02:56.06,Default,SideM,0000,0000,0000,,With plenty of bacon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.06,0:02:58.79,Default,Blonde,0000,0000,0000,,They had leek soup at the cafeteria today.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.79,0:03:00.60,Default,SideM,0000,0000,0000,,A mug full.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.60,0:03:01.58,Default,Blonde,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.58,0:03:02.62,Default,SideM,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.29,0:03:09.64,Default,SideM,0000,0000,0000,,What else did I have to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.64,0:03:16.52,Default,SideM,0000,0000,0000,,Pick a date to return the dragon, \Ncontact them, and then...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.29,0:03:19.08,Default,Space Walrus,0000,0000,0000,,You seem tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.34,0:03:22.75,Default,SideM,0000,0000,0000,,I hear Master's voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.97,0:03:25.89,Default,SideM,0000,0000,0000,,Meri.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.31,0:03:28.56,Default,SideM,0000,0000,0000,,Lindel.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.06,0:03:33.38,Default,Space Walrus,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry to exhaust you like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.46,0:03:36.41,Default,SideM,0000,0000,0000,,It was necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.84,0:03:39.05,Default,SideM,0000,0000,0000,,You can't leave that place.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.66,0:03:44.19,Default,SideM,0000,0000,0000,,Not until we find the next caretaker, \Nor the dragons go extinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.72,0:03:47.97,Default,Space Walrus,0000,0000,0000,,You're a kind child.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.45,0:03:54.17,Default,Space Walrus,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, I'm only here because I couldn't \Ncome to like the new times.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.88,0:03:56.11,Default,SideM,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.11,0:03:57.76,Default,Space Walrus,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be so conceding.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.34,0:04:00.31,Default,Space Walrus,0000,0000,0000,,What have you done wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.40,0:04:05.01,Default,SideM,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't become a mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.53,0:04:09.88,Default,SideM,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to be of use to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.16,0:04:14.60,Default,SideM,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a half-assed failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.31,0:04:18.77,Default,SideM,0000,0000,0000,,If I can't do this much,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.11,0:04:24.80,Default,SideM,0000,0000,0000,,I have no right to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.64,0:04:28.22,Default,Space Walrus,0000,0000,0000,,He's tired himself out and become a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.67,0:04:29.98,Default,Space Walrus,0000,0000,0000,,Silly you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.36,0:04:33.37,Default,Space Walrus,0000,0000,0000,,Really, first that redhead, now him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.37,0:04:35.09,Default,Space Walrus,0000,0000,0000,,Humans are strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.09,0:04:38.84,Default,Space Walrus,0000,0000,0000,,Why not just run away from what upsets you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.71,0:04:42.84,Default,Space Walrus,0000,0000,0000,,It's like they put effort into\N making themselves suffer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.00,0:04:48.10,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never figure that out, \Nno matter how old I get.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.99,0:04:53.72,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Now we just need to sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.09,0:04:55.68,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,That's it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.68,0:04:57.99,Default,Edgelady,0000,0000,0000,,Those are the instructions on the invitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.99,0:04:59.39,Default,Edgelady,0000,0000,0000,,We just have to do what it says.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.49,0:05:02.16,Default,Edgelady,0000,0000,0000,,Let's have faith in it for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.13,0:05:40.78,Default,Which?,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.09,0:05:42.42,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Marielle-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.42,0:05:45.52,Default,Groot,0000,0000,0000,,Greetings, young ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.15,0:05:50.25,Default,Groot,0000,0000,0000,,I am Phyllis, high priestess of the coven.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.25,0:05:53.18,Default,Groot,0000,0000,0000,,I'm something of a coordinator.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.26,0:05:57.44,Magus-Internal/narrator,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,This person's grown roots...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.66,0:06:00.77,Default,Edgelady,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for your invitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.14,0:06:02.71,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.00,0:06:05.63,Default,Groot,0000,0000,0000,,Marielle has told me that you're looking
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.63,0:06:11.76,Default,Groot,0000,0000,0000,,for a way to rid yourself of the \Ncurse without killing the dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.55,0:06:13.13,Default,Edgelady,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.06,0:06:20.69,Default,Groot,0000,0000,0000,,My apologies, but we have no \Nknowledge of how that may be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.15,0:06:22.40,Default,Which?,0000,0000,0000,,Phyllis!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.40,0:06:25.97,Default,Groot,0000,0000,0000,,Marielle, I appreciate your sentiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.36,0:06:31.15,Default,Groot,0000,0000,0000,,However, it would be uncouth\Nof us to ask for their aid
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.15,0:06:36.87,Default,Groot,0000,0000,0000,,when we can't grant their wishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.87,0:06:37.76,Default,Which?,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.83,0:06:41.95,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Aid?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.42,0:06:47.93,Default,Groot,0000,0000,0000,,I attempted to seal away the curse\Nthat has bound me to this tree,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.26,0:06:50.46,Default,Groot,0000,0000,0000,,but I failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.33,0:06:57.98,Default,Groot,0000,0000,0000,,Marielle is trying to use your \Ndragon's power to save me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.81,0:07:01.04,Default,Groot,0000,0000,0000,,Don't mind me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.41,0:07:03.73,Default,Groot,0000,0000,0000,,All people eventually perish.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.73,0:07:04.68,Default,Which?,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.79,0:07:06.69,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.24,0:07:13.47,Default,Groot,0000,0000,0000,,Worry about yourself for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.93,0:07:18.71,Default,Groot,0000,0000,0000,,It is right to save yourself \Nbefore you save others.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.69,0:07:23.88,Default,Groot,0000,0000,0000,,I have lived for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.88,0:07:27.46,Default,Groot,0000,0000,0000,,This state of mine is \Nsomething of a testament
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.46,0:07:31.63,Default,Groot,0000,0000,0000,,to the fact that I was able \Nto lend my hand to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.63,0:07:34.61,Default,Which?,0000,0000,0000,,Some of them weren't worth helping.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.61,0:07:36.22,Default,Groot,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.72,0:07:41.43,Default,Groot,0000,0000,0000,,But we have no way of knowing \Nwhat the future will bring.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.92,0:07:46.56,Default,Groot,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone has the freedom to choose their \Nown path and decide who they'd like to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.15,0:07:54.50,Default,Groot,0000,0000,0000,,Someday, that young lady there may\N cure someone else of their curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.93,0:08:00.03,Default,Groot,0000,0000,0000,,I will remain here, eagerly \Nawaiting such happy news.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.80,0:08:04.73,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Someone I know said something similar.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.73,0:08:08.81,Default,Groot,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's nice to know another agrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.25,0:08:10.03,Default,Edgelady,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.76,0:08:15.60,Default,Edgelady,0000,0000,0000,,As long as the dragon lives, if we \Ndon't even consider killing it,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.60,0:08:18.97,Default,Edgelady,0000,0000,0000,,we can neither undo nor return the curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.42,0:08:21.50,Default,Edgelady,0000,0000,0000,,Is that correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.68,0:08:24.79,Default,Groot,0000,0000,0000,,As far as we know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.93,0:08:29.37,Default,Groot,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize for turning you away \Nafter you've come so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.06,0:08:30.95,Default,Edgelady,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.95,0:08:34.53,Default,Edgelady,0000,0000,0000,,I thank you for allowing us\N to join your gathering.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.51,0:08:38.60,Default,Which?,0000,0000,0000,,Thorn...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.38,0:08:40.71,Default,Which?,0000,0000,0000,,As my apology...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.26,0:08:53.30,Default,Which?,0000,0000,0000,,It's difficult to have to choose \None or the other, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.27,0:09:06.60,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,We might not have gained\N anything from that,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.22,0:09:09.85,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,but let's keep trying.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.60,0:09:11.31,Default,Edgelady,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.89,0:09:14.18,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to go help with breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.13,0:09:28.84,Magus-Flashback-internal,Which?,0000,0000,0000,,The only thing that can replace \Na life is another life.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.59,0:09:41.28,Default,Dawwwwwwg,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going somewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.86,0:09:47.11,Default,Edgelady,0000,0000,0000,,Ruth, you would choose Chise \Nno matter what, would you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.78,0:09:49.78,Default,Dawwwwwwg,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.89,0:10:03.50,Default,Edgelady,0000,0000,0000,,Denizen of the wind, you're \Nthere, are you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.50,0:10:04.41,Default,Citizen,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.49,0:10:06.90,Default,Citizen,0000,0000,0000,,What a lovely evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.44,0:10:09.97,Default,Edgelady,0000,0000,0000,,Lend me your ability to \Nsee and smell the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.97,0:10:11.75,Default,Edgelady,0000,0000,0000,,Consume as much as you'd like.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.75,0:10:13.12,Default,Citizen,0000,0000,0000,,My, how generous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.85,0:10:16.98,Default,Citizen,0000,0000,0000,,I like the way you taste.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.56,0:12:11.86,Default,Priest,0000,0000,0000,,Ainsworth?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.85,0:12:13.90,Default,Edgeman,0000,0000,0000,,Simon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.90,0:12:15.60,Default,Priest,0000,0000,0000,,Glad I bumped into you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.60,0:12:17.45,Default,Priest,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to give this to Chise-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.65,0:12:20.94,Default,Priest,0000,0000,0000,,Has there been some good news?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.33,0:12:22.21,Default,Edgeman,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.14,0:12:25.30,Default,Priest,0000,0000,0000,,You have a clearer air about you,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.30,0:12:29.38,Default,Priest,0000,0000,0000,,like you have a goal in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.09,0:12:36.14,Default,Priest,0000,0000,0000,,You've seemed quite listless for \Nthe ten years I've known you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.07,0:12:41.12,Default,Edgeman,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose so.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.93,0:12:49.53,Magus-Internal/narrator,Edgeman,0000,0000,0000,,This may be the first time I've been \Ndriven to accomplish something.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.11,0:12:52.65,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, Elias!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.70,0:12:57.34,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,Perfect, I was about to go hang out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.34,0:12:59.79,Default,Edgeman,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, this is perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.66,0:13:03.71,Default,Edgeman,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have to search for you anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.30,0:13:14.90,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Count to seven and eight...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.48,0:13:22.19,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,In the dream in which the child sleeps.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.19,0:13:29.35,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Let's find and count the flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.35,0:13:37.29,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Mommy will give you a bouquet of flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.20,0:13:45.04,Default,Citizen,0000,0000,0000,,What an awful smell.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.46,0:13:47.94,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Ariel.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.94,0:13:49.25,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Long time no see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.17,0:13:51.83,Default,Citizen,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.18,0:13:54.86,Default,Citizen,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to your body? You look awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.52,0:13:59.16,Default,Citizen,0000,0000,0000,,You wouldn't have ended up like \Nthis if you'd come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.87,0:14:01.02,Default,Citizen,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.78,0:14:06.29,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.29,0:14:07.44,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be fine soon enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.31,0:14:11.34,Default,Citizen,0000,0000,0000,,It's like you've been reborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.34,0:14:13.68,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,I decided to be more positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.08,0:14:15.11,Default,Citizen,0000,0000,0000,,Good girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.75,0:14:26.05,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Ariel, you wouldn't have worried about me \Nif I hadn't been a Sleigh Beggy, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.77,0:14:27.89,Default,Citizen,0000,0000,0000,,So what?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.44,0:14:33.39,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Elias is up to something.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.91,0:14:35.57,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Without telling me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.12,0:14:37.17,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,By himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.31,0:14:40.38,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,We agreed to do this together.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.98,0:14:42.82,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Ruth might be in on it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.80,0:14:44.67,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.83,0:14:52.03,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,I want someone who will do as I say, \Nno matter what happens to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.42,0:14:53.25,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.74,0:14:55.23,Default,Citizen,0000,0000,0000,,Why me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.30,0:15:02.29,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,You like Sleigh Beggies, not me specifically. \NOtherwise, you wouldn't side with Elias, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.65,0:15:10.11,Default,Citizen,0000,0000,0000,,You're not wrong, but I like {\i1}you{\i0} too, Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.11,0:15:11.51,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.51,0:15:14.50,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,I guess that means I can't give you the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.50,0:15:18.04,Default,Citizen,0000,0000,0000,,So you're going to ask the same\N thing of someone else?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.04,0:15:20.12,Default,Citizen,0000,0000,0000,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.76,0:15:24.64,Default,Dawwwwwwg,0000,0000,0000,,What are you about to do, Elias?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.16,0:15:26.97,Default,Edgeman,0000,0000,0000,,Chise won't last.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.65,0:15:33.02,Default,Edgeman,0000,0000,0000,,This is the only way for us not to lose her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.92,0:15:35.92,Default,Edgeman,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Ruth?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.02,0:15:39.51,Default,Dawwwwwwg,0000,0000,0000,,The answer's obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.17,0:15:44.01,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Elia—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.42,0:15:45.08,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Stella!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.56,0:15:46.03,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Why—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.32,0:15:47.29,Default,Edgeman,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.91,0:15:55.01,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Elias...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.34,0:15:57.52,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Ruth...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.48,0:15:59.27,Default,Dawwwwwwg,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.88,0:16:04.37,Default,Dawwwwwwg,0000,0000,0000,,When you wake up, everything \Nshould be better.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.28,0:16:09.89,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,No... don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.25,0:16:20.45,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Nevin.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.45,0:16:22.02,Default,Necrogroot,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.46,0:16:26.02,Default,Necrogroot,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be able to stand and catch up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.02,0:16:31.03,Default,Necrogroot,0000,0000,0000,,Your ability to do so is growing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.48,0:16:35.58,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm really scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.76,0:16:39.09,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to know what \NI'll find when I catch up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.60,0:16:42.23,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,What Elias is trying to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.20,0:16:44.75,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,What is he doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.42,0:16:47.51,Default,Necrogroot,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.51,0:16:53.61,Default,Necrogroot,0000,0000,0000,,What matters is to always be \Nclear on what {\i1}you{\i0} need to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.55,0:17:00.76,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you always come for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.31,0:17:05.07,Default,Necrogroot,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not guiding you at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.75,0:17:11.58,Default,Necrogroot,0000,0000,0000,,The me that exists here is the me that \Nyou've allowed to live inside your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.36,0:17:16.20,Default,Necrogroot,0000,0000,0000,,You are the one guiding yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.03,0:17:22.77,Default,Necrogroot,0000,0000,0000,,You need not drown yourself in hardships.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.20,0:17:27.84,Default,Necrogroot,0000,0000,0000,,Fly strong across the stormy oceans.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.17,0:17:33.30,Default,Necrogroot,0000,0000,0000,,What is it that you've decided you must do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.70,0:17:37.27,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,First, I need to know what \NElias is trying to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.88,0:17:41.14,Default,Necrogroot,0000,0000,0000,,Now, go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.41,0:17:58.09,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Everything will better when I wake up, \Nwhen I haven't done anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.57,0:18:04.57,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing so magical has ever \Nhappened to me before.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.88,0:18:11.89,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Silky.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.73,0:18:17.90,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.09,0:18:33.18,Default,Edgeman,0000,0000,0000,,Ruth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.18,0:18:34.25,Default,Edgeman,0000,0000,0000,,Get Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.25,0:18:35.10,Default,Dawwwwwwg,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.83,0:18:36.96,Default,Dawwwwwwg,0000,0000,0000,,She's awake.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.45,0:18:40.09,Default,Best Villain Nominee,0000,0000,0000,,That's odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.46,0:18:45.89,Default,Best Villain Nominee,0000,0000,0000,,You called me a monster, \Nand now you do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.17,0:18:47.15,Default,Edgeman,0000,0000,0000,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.93,0:18:49.97,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Elias!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.22,0:18:51.40,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Elias!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.40,0:18:56.39,Default,Best Villain Nominee,0000,0000,0000,,If I'm a monster for serving \Nmyself at the expense of others...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.42,0:19:00.21,Default,Best Villain Nominee,0000,0000,0000,,Then I knew it! You're a monster, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.38,0:19:02.49,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Elias!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.13,0:19:10.83,Default,Best Villain Nominee,0000,0000,0000,,Help me, Chise!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.11,0:19:12.30,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Stella.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.30,0:19:15.84,Default,Best Villain Nominee,0000,0000,0000,,Elias wants to sacrifice me in your place.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.27,0:19:19.28,Default,Best Villain Nominee,0000,0000,0000,,He says he's going to transfer \Nyour curse to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.79,0:19:22.71,Default,Best Villain Nominee,0000,0000,0000,,He's going to kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.30,0:19:26.57,Default,Edgeman,0000,0000,0000,,Chise, get away from her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.57,0:19:27.47,Default,Edgeman,0000,0000,0000,,She's...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.47,0:19:28.34,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Elias.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.26,0:19:33.93,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Elias, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.86,0:19:47.64,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Stella, I'll catch up to you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.64,0:19:49.70,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Run as far as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.70,0:19:51.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.19,0:19:52.41,Default,Edgeman,0000,0000,0000,,Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.41,0:19:53.80,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Don't come near me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.80,0:19:56.11,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,You don't go, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.67,0:20:03.21,Default,Edgeman,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.62,0:20:05.56,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,About what?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.08,0:20:10.04,Default,Edgeman,0000,0000,0000,,For trying to sacrifice \NStella in your place.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.11,0:20:19.07,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted you to let me think \Nabout this together with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.99,0:20:22.44,Default,Edgeman,0000,0000,0000,,I never promised anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.87,0:20:25.71,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Wh...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.61,0:20:27.83,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Are you...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.02,0:20:32.29,Default,Edgeman,0000,0000,0000,,I'd decided if it had to be\N done, it would be Stella.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.33,0:20:37.78,Default,Edgeman,0000,0000,0000,,You look at Stella with a different \Nexpression than you do me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.28,0:20:40.29,Default,Edgeman,0000,0000,0000,,I can't stand that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.75,0:20:43.64,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.81,0:20:48.51,Default,Edgeman,0000,0000,0000,,As long as you'll live, I'm happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.80,0:21:01.86,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,You were no different.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.13,0:21:06.38,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Ariel.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.38,0:21:07.03,Default,Edgeman,0000,0000,0000,,Chise!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.62,0:21:09.91,Default,Citizen,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't going anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.47,0:21:13.93,Default,Citizen,0000,0000,0000,,You fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.66,0:21:18.93,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Stella.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.82,0:21:23.71,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Car...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.40,0:21:25.66,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Joseph...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.44,0:21:29.94,Default,Best Villain Nominee,0000,0000,0000,,Shucks, you got me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.94,0:21:32.65,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you doing this to Stella?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.13,0:21:34.80,Default,Best Villain Nominee,0000,0000,0000,,Let's make a deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.80,0:21:36.15,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,A deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.64,0:21:44.00,Default,Best Villain Nominee,0000,0000,0000,,If you agree, I'll give you a spell \Nthat'll ward off your inevitable death,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.00,0:21:46.05,Default,Best Villain Nominee,0000,0000,0000,,and I'll give this girl back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.05,0:21:46.73,Default,Best Villain Nominee,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.49,0:21:49.20,Default,Best Villain Nominee,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.72,0:21:51.87,Default,Best Villain Nominee,0000,0000,0000,,You understand, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.68,0:21:53.78,Default,Edgeman,0000,0000,0000,,Chise!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.25,0:21:57.77,Default,Best Villain Nominee,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, they're going catch up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.36,0:22:00.87,Default,Best Villain Nominee,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.37,0:22:02.89,Default,Edgeman,0000,0000,0000,,Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.60,0:22:16.51,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,I can't be with you as you are now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.73,0:23:58.66,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,The girl parts ways with the mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.66,0:24:04.14,Default,Cheese,0000,0000,0000,,She follows Joseph down into \Nthe nightmare that torments her.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.81,0:24:06.20,Default,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.74,0:24:09.30,Default,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me, Chise.
